race.description: Gorski Hardox Tough Tippers 5Th Grade H
race.comment: LEAD FOOT LARRY (1) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing sixth (30.67) last time in a Grade 5 at Albion Park. Has never missed the frame at the trip from three starts. Worth another chance. SANTORINI BEACH (7) was strongly fancied latest and proved too good with a 1.75 lengths win at this track in a handy 19.26. Draws out wide but goes well at this distance. Capable of going well again. MR. MARVELLOUS (8) looks close to another win after finishing second last time (19.30) at this track. Overall form off this box is sound. Meets a moderate line up and should run well. CLIFF CLAVIN (3) will give backers a sight.
